{
  "stem": "19923.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 104.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Joe, my older brother Joe, and Fanny used to go together, and Martin and I used to go together.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I was Martin's big brother, and Joe was Fanny's big brother.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we-- of course, I was very close to Martin, very close to Martin, and Joe was very close to Fanny.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Although we were in-- in the family close to each other, most of my disagreements or arguments would be with Martin over toys or things that happened.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I wouldn't have too much with Joe, except Joe was the domineering person, and he carried that on into adult life.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He was the big brother.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And big brother, he had to tell you what to do.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Of course, you let him do that for a while.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But eventually, you know, you get big enough to be able to make your own decisions.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But my early recollections in those years was-- was of pairing off-- Martin and I and Joe and Fanny.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Antisemitism in Germany is hard for anyone who has not lived through to grasp.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But the Germans in Germany had a lot of swear words that they would use that would get under your skin, and they lived with you.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And [GERMAN] Jude, you know, [GERMAN], all these things.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I mean, at an earliest age, I was exposed to that type of antisemitism.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I knew all the words that they would hurl at you when they saw you.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We-- when we traveled in the streets, it was-- if-- you had to be pretty fast, because if any Germans saw you they would immediately start throwing stones at you.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You'd become a target.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And you learn at an earliest life that when you run from the stones, you don't run in a straight line.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
